Sentencas: Two series of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) were prepared, one with a composite cathode layer of lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM) and yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) on top and the other further has a LSM current collector layer on top.
Titulo: The Effect of Humidity and Oxygen Partial Pressure on LSM-YSZ Cathode

Sentencas: The fuel cells were heat treated at 1,000 C in air or nitrogen choosing dry or humid (70% steam) conditions.
Titulo: The Effect of Humidity and Oxygen Partial Pressure on LSM-YSZ Cathode

Sentencas: XRD, SEM, and XPS investigations were performed on the various samples.
Titulo: The Effect of Humidity and Oxygen Partial Pressure on LSM-YSZ Cathode

Sentencas: The most severe modifications were observed in humid nitrogen atmosphere at low oxygen partial pressure.
Titulo: The Effect of Humidity and Oxygen Partial Pressure on LSM-YSZ Cathode

Sentencas: LSM surface change goes along with a decrease of manganese concentration and strontium enrichment on the surface of the materials.
Titulo: The Effect of Humidity and Oxygen Partial Pressure on LSM-YSZ Cathode

Sentencas: Formation of monoclinic zirconia and zirconate phases was also observed.
Titulo: The Effect of Humidity and Oxygen Partial Pressure on LSM-YSZ Cathode

Sentencas: These results give a closer insight into possible degradation mechanisms of SOFC composite cathode materials in dependence of humidity and oxygen partial pressure.
Titulo: The Effect of Humidity and Oxygen Partial Pressure on LSM-YSZ Cathode
